HEADWORD: Jakie
<hw>Ja"kie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
South American striped frog (<spn>Pseudis paradoxa</spn>), remarkable
for having a tadpole larger than the adult, and hence called also
<altname>paradoxical frog</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

